1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we are going to apply what we've learned thus far by setting up our pages,

2
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:09,400
posts, site logo and navigation menu.

3
00:00:11,760 --> 00:00:14,760
First up, let's create our pages.

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:16,600
I'll make my way to pages, click on Add New Page and then once I do that, I will be able

5
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:23,840
to add or select a pattern that comes with my theme and I'm using the Twenty Twenty-Four default theme.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
So I'll go ahead and select a pattern that appeals to me and name it Home.

7
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:38,320
After publishing, I'll make my way back to pages and add my next page.

8
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:45,040
This time I'm not going to choose a pattern and I'll name this page Blog.

9
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:50,080
Next, I'm going to create an About page and select the relevant pattern.

10
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:56,240
And lastly, I will also create a Contact page without choosing a pattern.

11
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:07,440
Now I have my pages in place.

12
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:14,280
So next, I'm going to make my way to Settings and click on Reading.

13
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:19,840
And for my home page display, I will select a static page and set my Home page as my static

14
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:28,040
home page and my Blog page as my posts page.

15
00:01:31,820 --> 00:01:34,820
Just a reminder, if you have selected your latest posts for your home page display, you

16
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:40,200
will modify the blog home template for this home page or front page as no page has been

17
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:46,160
created.

18
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:49,120
Please note, when we open up our static home page and open the settings sidebar, we will

19
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,400
notice that this page has been assigned to the page template or the default page template

20
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:05,480
and my blog page or posts page has been assigned to the blog home template and this cannot

21
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:11,160
be changed.

22
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
And then we'll also notice that my other pages have also been assigned to the general

23
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,800
or default page template, the same as my Home page.

24
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:27,560
Next let's shift our attention to posts and as you will notice, I've already created two

25
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:32,080
posts as well as categories and tags.

26
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:40,840
Just a reminder, categories are used to classify content into main topics or sections and tags

27
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:46,440
are like labels that give specific details about content.

28
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:51,360
As an example, I'm going to go ahead and add a new post.

29
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:56,500
The post is about New York and then I will add some dummy content.

30
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:02,960
Thereafter, I will open up the settings sidebar and select the relevant category, in this

31
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:09,360
case Travel and I will add a new tag, namely City.

32
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,480
Lastly, I will set the featured image or the post thumbnail.

33
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,800
The featured image is of course the representative image for your post and once set, we can hit

34
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:30,760
publish and then view our three posts with their relevant categories and tags.

35
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Next, let's take a closer look at the navigation menu and make our way to Appearance and then

36
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:46,520
click on Editor.

37
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,000
This will open up the Site Editor and on the right, we will notice our Home page and if

38
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
we open up our Home page, we will see the dummy content or the pattern that we added when

39
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:59,840
we created the page.

40
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,800
And at the top, we see the header pattern provided by our theme.

41
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:06,400
And if we try to edit this header, we will see a message that says Edit your template

42
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:11,840
to edit this block.

43
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:12,920
So let's go ahead and click on Edit template.

44
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:16,560
And now we can edit the header for the Page template.

45
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:20,160
Please note, this header will also be found on the Blog Home template.

46
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:23,760
So if we make any changes to this header in the page template, it will also automatically

47
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:29,640
update in the blog home template.

48
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:33,120
As we can see, we have our navigation menu top right and the great thing is this navigation

49
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:38,320
menu was added automatically when we created our pages.

50
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:43,960
When we select our navigation menu and open up the List View, we will notice that the navigation

51
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:50,240
items are still part of a page list.

52
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:53,400
So to change this, click on Edit in your settings sidebar to detach the page list so

53
00:04:57,520 --> 00:05:00,520
that you can manage navigation items individually.

54
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:04,560
Once detached, you can use the List View to reorder navigation items.

55
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:11,760
Or you can use the arrows of the navigation block toolbar to reposition items where you

56
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:17,720
want them.

57
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:19,760
Next, I've decided to add social links to my navigation menu.

58
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:25,320
So when I click on the Inserter of the Navigation block, I will insert a Social Icons block

59
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,600
and then select the relevant social media platforms.

60
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:35,520
In this case, X and Instagram.

61
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:40,640
And don't forget to add the relevant URLs.

62
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:47,400
When you select the Navigation block, you can click on the three vertical dots in your

63
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:51,640
settings sidebar to create a new menu or select one of your existing menus.

64
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:58,400
When you select Settings, you will be able to change the justification or alignment as

65
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:03,640
well as the orientation of your navigation menu.

66
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:07,440
Below that, you can also select a hamburger menu that will appear when your site is viewed

67
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:12,320
on a smaller device.

68
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:14,880
When you click on Styles, you have a variety of options to style your navigation menu

69
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:19,280
further.

70
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:20,440
Next, let's talk about the Site Logo block.

71
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:24,600
As you will notice, the header pattern that was provided by my theme includes a Site Logo

72
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:29,400
block.

73
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:30,520
Click on the Site Logo block to add a new image from your media library or to upload one

74
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:35,520
directly from your computer.

75
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:37,600
I will go ahead and upload a logo that I've already added to my desktop.

76
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:44,440
And then I will enlarge it slightly.

77
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:47,960
Next, I would also like to add my navigation menu to my footer.

78
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,600
So when we scroll down, we will notice that there are some dummy content below quick links,

79
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:59,920
which was part of my default footer pattern that came with my theme.

80
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:04,960
So when I open the List View and select the Navigation block, I can click on the three

81
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:09,600
vertical dots in my settings sidebar and then select the relevant navigation menu.

82
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:19,520
Now my navigation menus are in place in my header and footer.

83
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,920
And as mentioned before, if we make our way to the blog home template, which is the template

84
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,400
for my posts page, we will see that the header and the footer are the same.

85
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:39,160
Once we have all these elements in place, we want to decide on an overall style for

86
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:44,280
our website.

87
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:46,120
So when we make our way to Styles, you can customize the typography colors and layout

88
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:53,320
of your site.

89
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:54,320
Or if you click on Browse Styles, you'll be able to see a zoomed out view of all the

90
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:00,760
different style combinations that come with your theme.

91
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,360
I will go ahead and select the Rust style as an example.

92
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:18,920
Now that we have our pages, posts, navigation menu, site logo and style in place, we can

93
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:25,680
go ahead and start adding content to our pages and modifying some of the patterns that we've

94
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:32,120
added.

95
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:35,280
And for a page like our Contact page with no pattern, we can start building from scratch.

96
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:43,040
And to modify how we want our posts to be displayed, we need to make our way to the blog

97
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:48,920
home template.

98
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:52,280
And when we open up our blog home template, we can customize our blog page as well as

99
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:58,760
the Query Loop block to decide how we want our blog posts or dynamic content to be displayed.

